The suspect reportedly declined efforts to identify himself before Suneka Deputy OCS. [Courtesy]  A man passing himself off as an officer of the Kenya Defence Forces (KDF) was held for harassing a female police officer and creating disturbance in Kisii.  The imposter is being held at Suneka Police Station in Kisii for allegedly assaulting a police officer he claimed was not dressed appropriately while manning the police desk.  The suspect is said to have stormed Suneka Police Station Report Office and dragged the police officer out, saying she was not dressed appropriately and that he was a KDF officer.  According to a police report, the alleged imposter drove into the station at around 9pm on Monday night, parked his car right in front of the police post, and stormed the reporting desk.  Leaders now plotting their survival beyond 2022 elections  There is nothing unusual with military officers doing civilian jobs  Kisii Senator Sam Ongeri finally launches bid for governor  Pregnant wife of KDF soldier stabbed to death "The intruder violently pulled the female officer from her duty post which prompted her colleague and officer on duty to immediately intervene," read the police report in part.  When confronted, the 27-year-old suspect reportedly declined to identify himself before Suneka Police Station Deputy OCS and Inspector of Police, Cephas Ombija.  Directorate of Criminal Investigations (DCI) officers are reportedly questioning the suspect to establish if he has connection to acts of crime in the area.   By  Isaiah Gwengi | 3 hours ago By Harold Odhiambo | 4 hours ago By Isaiah Gwengi | 1 day ago By James Omoro | 1 day ago